FBIS3-53964 "drnes014_l_94008" FBIS-NES-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 ISRAEL Peres: Referendum Will Not Tie Government's Hands TA2001153994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 20 Jan 94 TA2001153994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres said that a national referendum on the Golan Heights would not prevent the government from reaching a decision on the issue, nor would it tie the government's hands in the negotiations. When asked whether or not he was in favor of a national referendum, Peres replied: We will decide at the appropriate time. I am not rejecting the idea out of hand. The foreign minister was speaking at Bet Berl during a ceremony in which scholarships were awarded to Jewish and Arab students.
